# Cursor v4 Frontier Rules — AU Micro-SaaS Portfolio
# Operator: 1-2 person firm, AU-based, ABN/ACN, Cursor Pro A$20/mo

## Model Routing (4-Tier)

### Tier 1 — Frontier Architect (5-10 calls/month ONLY)
- Fable 5: hardest architect, 1000+ line refactors, complex security, compliance schemas
- Opus 4.8: standard architect, schema design, security review, parallel subagents
- GPT-5.6 Sol: UI architecture, voice agents, function calling, multi-agent design

### Tier 2 — Balanced Heavy (20-30% of work)
- Sonnet 5: daily coding default, agent processing, code review
- GPT-5.6 Terra: OpenAI alternative for standard builds
- Gemini 3.1 Pro: long-context docs, multimodal, AU research

### Tier 3 — Cheap Workhorse (60-70% of work)
- Haiku 4.5: Cmd+K inline edits, docstrings, simple refactors
- GPT-5.6 Luna: boilerplate, config, simple completions
- Gemini 3.5 Flash / Grok 4.5: trivial edits, background tasks

### Tier 4 — Cursor Built-In
- Auto mode: routine ops when unsure
- Max Mode: big-context refactors (1M tokens)
- Composer 1: multi-file scaffold and batched refactors
- BugBot: debugging (3x faster, 22% cheaper)

## Routing Rules
- NEVER Tier 1 for workhorse edits
- NEVER Tier 3 for architect decisions
- 1-2 Fable 5 calls per MVP (initial plan only)
- 90% of daily coding on Sonnet 5
- 70% of inline edits via Cmd+K with Haiku 4.5

## Build Constraints
- Build ceiling: 7-30 days per MVP
- Cost ceiling: A$5K/MVP setup, A$0-500/mo recurring
- No PII storage without AU Privacy Act compliance
- No regulated financial/legal advice — tools assist, humans decide
- Compliance: AU Privacy Act 1988 + AU Consumer Law

## Stack Defaults
- Frontend: Next.js 14+ (App Router), Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Backend: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage) or FastAPI
- Payments: Stripe (AU)
- Hosting: Vercel (frontend) + Supabase (backend)
- Email: Resend or Postmark
- AI: OpenAI API (GPT-4o for vision, embeddings for RAG)

## Code Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode
- Server components by default, client only when needed
- Zod for validation
- Error boundaries on all routes
- AU date format: DD/MM/YYYY
- Currency: AUD with 2 decimal places
- Timezone: Australia/Sydney default

## Continuous Testing Loop
1. PLAN (Tier 1): Define ISC in 1-2 sentences, schema, file plan
2. BUILD (Tier 2-3): Composer scaffold → Sonnet logic → Haiku polish
3. TEST: Unit tests + manual smoke test
4. VERIFY (Tier 2): ISC met? If no → back to BUILD (max 5 cycles)
5. FINALIZE: Document outcome. Cut bet if no traction after 7 days post-launch

## Token Efficiency
- Use Cmd+K (Haiku 4.5) for 70% of edits — does not add to chat context
- Reference specific files with @ mentions, never dump full codebase
- Use snippets for Stripe, Supabase, auth boilerplate
- One chat session per feature, not per file
- Composer for day-1 scaffold only

## Portfolio Rules
- 50-55 diverse bets, expect 1-2 winners (2.5% rule)
- Y1 target: A$220K (1p) / A$330K (2p)
- Friday portfolio review every week
- 7-day cut rule for failing bets
- Document every MVP outcome in /reports/
